    "synopsis": "The Iron Hands cruiser Sisypheum has become a vessel of shattered Legion warriors — Iron Hands, a Salamander, a Raven Guard — bound together by Captain Ulrach Branthan's stasis-locked body and a vendetta that has outlived every chain of command. When the warlord Shadrak Meduson summons them to strike at a hidden Alpha Legion outpost, the crew agrees almost without debate. They are tired of running. They want a victory. But the outpost is not a depot, the operation is not what Meduson described, and Alpharius's sons have built the entire engagement around an answer to a question the loyalists did not know they were asking. The story closes around the Sisypheum like a snare, and the architect waiting at the centre is unlike any opponent the shattered have faced.",
